================================================================================
✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: OBSERVATION MODELS WITH PYMDP INTEGRATION
================================================================================
🔍 OBSERVATION MODEL FOUNDATIONS:
1. A matrices encode P(observation | state) using PyMDP obj_array structure
2. Perfect observation: identity matrix (entropy=0, minimal VFE)
3. Noise/ambiguity: off-diagonal entries increase entropy and VFE
4. Information content: lower entropy = better state discrimination
5. Multi-modal: separate A matrices provide complementary information
6. Partial observability: indirect observation requires inference

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. Agent class seamlessly handles multi-modal observations
8. Multi-factor state spaces enable complex environment modeling
9. Control factors allow selective action over state dimensions
10. Proprioceptive observations provide agent self-awareness
11. Generative process/model separation enables realistic simulations
12. PyMDP validation: is_normalized() and validate_model() ensure correctness

🔬 PyMDP Methods Demonstrated & Validated:
- pymdp.agent.Agent() with multi-modal A matrices
- pymdp.utils.obj_array_zeros() for proper A matrix structure
- pymdp.utils.sample() for realistic observation generation
- pymdp.maths.softmax() for probabilistic observation models
- pymdp.maths.entropy() for information analysis
- pymdp.maths.kl_div() for discriminability measurement
- Agent.infer_states() for multi-modal state inference
- Following agent_demo.py patterns for real PyMDP usage

✨ Enhancements Added:
- Complete PyMDP Agent class integration with multi-modal observations
